The paper deals with the analysis of social networks and web graphs, which are typical topics in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). The paper also uses algorithms and software tools to approximate the number of reachable pairs and the distribution of distances in a graph, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI, cs.SD, and cs.SOC, followed by cs.DS and cs.IR.
